    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-21T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-21T11:40:00-05:00" n="853"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/836: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-21T17:00:00+00:20"
                            >December 21, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 21—3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>320. Foreign Office has just given me in strict confidence text of British note
                    replying to Dutch note of protest reported in my 287, November 22, 5 p.m.
                    Essence of British note is claim that a belligerent’s right of retaliation which
                    inherently constitutes a departure from ordinary rules is well recognized in
                    international law and that British reprisal measures have a similar objective,
                    and consequently are the most appropriate counter to Germany’s illegal attempts
                    to stop all maritime trade with Britain. The Dutch assertion that these measures
                    are of “an odious character” appears to have markedly irritated the British.</p>
                <p>Text of note by tomorrow’s pouch.<note n="73" xml:id="d853fn73">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
